Author: tlrobinson
Content:
JavaScript, at least up until recently.

It definitely got a bad reputation due to it's inappropriate name (trying to jump on the Java bandwagon, nothing to with Java whatsoever), copy/paste JavaScript snippets of the late 90s (giving us exciting features like blinking/scrolling text, fun cursors, etc), ginormous browser inconsistencies, and the use of prototypal inheritance instead of classical inheritance.

Author: rms
Content: This is a straight PR move on EAs part. I haven't seen anyone from OLPC actually say that Sim City is included. I suspect it is accessible to OLPC children the same way it is accessible free to us -- http://simcity.ea.com/play/simcity_classic.php, because I sincerely doubt that OLPC would install non-free software on every laptop they distribute.
